const faqItems = [
  {
    q: "What types of kitchen are popular in Henley-in-Arden?",
    a: "Henley-in-Arden's housing stock divides broadly into two categories, each with its own kitchen style. Period properties — the medieval and timber-framed buildings along the High Street, Georgian and Victorian houses in the town, and farmhouse-style properties in the surrounding villages of Ullenhall, Beaudesert, and Tanworth-in-Arden — tend to favour heritage-style kitchens: painted in-frame, shaker, or farmhouse designs in neutral tones such as sage green, off-white, stone, and dusky blue. These kitchens often use traditional materials — solid oak or painted MDF in-frame doors, stone or granite worktops, a Belfast or butler sink, and a range cooker as the focal point. The second category covers larger rural detached properties and converted barns, where bespoke or premium semi-bespoke installations are common, with handleless or slab-door cabinetry, quartz worktops, and fully integrated appliance banks. Pindi is equally experienced with both approaches.",
  },
  {
    q: "How much does kitchen fitting cost in Henley-in-Arden?",
    a: "Kitchen fitting costs near Henley-in-Arden vary considerably depending on the size and complexity of the project. A straightforward 12–15 unit kitchen in a modern rural home will typically sit in the £1,500–£2,500 range for labour. A larger heritage-style installation in a period property — where work involves scribing around exposed beams, fitting around stone flag floors, or managing irregular wall angles — will be priced higher to reflect the additional time and skill involved. Bespoke and premium installations in larger rural properties or barn conversions will be higher still. Pindi provides a fully itemised, fixed-price quote following a pre-installation survey, which is the only accurate way to price a kitchen in a property with period features. See the kitchen fitting costs page for full detail on the variables involved.",
  },
  {
    q: "Do you cover B95 and the surrounding Arden villages?",
    a: "Yes. Pindi covers the B95 postcode in full, which includes Henley-in-Arden town itself and the surrounding rural area. He also covers the adjacent villages and parishes including Beaudesert, Ullenhall, Tanworth-in-Arden, Lapworth, Wootton Wawen, and Preston Bagot. Henley-in-Arden is approximately 18 miles from Pindi's base in Coventry, a straightforward drive via the A41 and A3400, and approximately 14 miles from Solihull. Rural properties and farm settings are not a problem — Pindi is used to working with restricted access, long drives, and the logistical considerations that come with remote rural locations. Call 07399 651836 to confirm coverage for your specific address.",
  },
  {
    q: "How do period property features affect kitchen installation?",
    a: "Period properties in and around Henley-in-Arden present a specific set of challenges that require experience and careful planning to manage well. Exposed beams at varying heights mean that wall unit heights must be individually calculated and cabinets may need to be scribed or notched to fit around timber. Stone flag floors are rarely level — sometimes by as much as 40–50mm across a kitchen — which means base units must be individually shimmed and levelled, and plinths cut to profile rather than set to a standard height. Original walls in timber-framed and stone buildings are rarely plumb, square, or flat, so the usual approach of aligning cabinets and worktops to the wall simply does not work; everything must be set out from a true level and plumb reference instead. Chimney breasts and inglenooks create irregular alcoves that must be incorporated into the design. These are not problems that can be solved by the kitchen plan alone — they require a fitter who has encountered them before, knows what to look for during the survey, and has the practical skills to adapt on the day.",
  },
  {
    q: "Which kitchen retailers do you fit near Henley-in-Arden?",
    a: "Pindi fits kitchens from every major UK retailer and manufacturer. Near Henley-in-Arden the most common choices are Howdens Joinery (particularly their in-frame and painted shaker ranges, which suit the area's period properties), Wren Kitchens, and Magnet. He also fits premium and specialist brands including Masterclass, Mereway, Neptune, and deVOL — all of which are popular in Henley's larger rural properties and barn conversions. Benchmarx is another frequent choice for rural projects, particularly where the Benchmarx depot's trade supply model aligns well with a project's timing. Because Pindi is fully independent, the choice of retailer is entirely yours — he brings the same standard of workmanship regardless of the brand. See the Howdens installation page or the Wren installation page for more detail, or call 07399 651836 to discuss your specific kitchen.",
  },
];

const internalLinks = [
  {
    label: "Book a pre-installation survey",
    href: "/survey/",
    description: "£195 survey credited back in full when you proceed — the essential first step for any period property",
  },
  {
    label: "Kitchen fitting costs explained",
    href: "/costs/",
    description: "Fully itemised guide to what affects kitchen installation prices, including period property work",
  },
  {
    label: "Stratford-upon-Avon area page",
