          The Survey-First Process — Essential in Period and Rural Properties
        </h2>
        <p class="leading-relaxed mb-4" style="color: var(--text-soft);">
          Every kitchen fitting project begins with a pre-installation survey carried out by Pindi personally. The survey costs £195 and is credited back in full if you proceed with the installation. For properties around Henley-in-Arden, the survey is not merely recommended — it is essential. The variables present in period and rural properties make it impossible to produce an accurate, fixed-price quote without visiting the room in person.
        </p>
        <p class="leading-relaxed mb-4" style="color: var(--text-soft);">
          During the survey, Pindi takes precise room measurements, checks ceiling heights and any beam positions that affect wall unit placement, inspects the floor condition and level variation, reviews your kitchen plan and elevation drawings, and identifies any work that will need to be done before or alongside the installation. For period properties this typically includes flagging any floor levelling compound requirements, identifying beam positions that affect wall unit height, checking whether the plumbing routes will work with the planned sink position, and noting any wall surfaces that may require additional preparation before cabinet fixing.
        </p>
        <p class="leading-relaxed mb-4" style="color: var(--text-soft);">
          After the survey you receive a written, fixed-price quote that reflects the actual conditions of your room. The price does not change unless you change the scope of the work. In a complex period property, this certainty is particularly valuable.
        </p>
        <p class="leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--text-soft);">
          Survey appointments in the Henley-in-Arden area are available within two weeks. To book, call <a href="tel:07399651836" class="font-semibold" style="color: var(--teal);">07399 651836</a> or visit the <a href="/survey/" class="font-semibold" style="color: var(--teal);">survey booking page</a>.
        </p>
